    "comments": [
        {
            "topic": "FUNCTION",
            "text": "Involved in the virus replication. Contains a helicase domain and a methyltransferase domain. The methyltransferase domain is probably involved in viral RNA capping. Involved in the formation of ER membrane spherular invaginations in which RNA replication complexes form (By similarity). {ECO:0000250}."
        },
        {
            "topic": "SUBUNIT",
            "text": "Interacts with RNA-directed RNA polymerase 2a (By similarity). Interacts with Arabidopsis TIP1-1, TIP1-2, TIP1-3, TIP2-1, TIP2-2 and TIP2-3. {ECO:0000250, ECO:0000269|PubMed:17030879}."
        },
        {
            "topic": "SUBCELLULAR LOCATION",
            "text": "Host endoplasmic reticulum membrane {ECO:0000250}; Peripheral membrane protein {ECO:0000250}."
        },
        {
            "topic": "SIMILARITY",
            "text": "Belongs to the bromoviridae replication protein 1a family. {ECO:0000305}."
        }
    ],
